# Design Tokens — Zero Hardcoded Values

## Two Sources of Truth

| Category | Source | Usage |
|----------|--------|-------|
| Spacing | Tailwind | `@apply p-4 gap-2` |
| Sizing | Tailwind | `@apply w-full min-h-screen` |
| Radius | Tailwind | `@apply rounded-md` |
| Shadows | Tailwind | `@apply shadow-sm` |
| z-index | Tailwind | `@apply z-10`, `@apply z-30`, `@apply z-40` |
| Opacity | Tailwind | `@apply opacity-70` |
| Scale | Tailwind | `@apply scale-95` |
| Display | Tailwind | `@apply hidden`, `@apply block` |
| Transitions | Tailwind | `@apply transition-all duration-200 ease-in-out` |
| **ALL colors** | **Primer via useTheme** | `var(--primer-fg-default)`, `var(--primer-canvas-subtle)` |
| **ALL border colors** | **Primer via useTheme** | `var(--primer-border-default)` |
| **Color adjustments** | Primer tokens | Use a different `--primer-*` token (e.g., `canvas-inset` instead of `canvas-default`) |
| Layout dimensions | Global CSS vars | `var(--layout-sidebar-width)` |

## No Custom Token Files

NEVER create SCSS token files, variable maps, or custom design systems.

**Exception — Breakpoint SCSS variables:** `src/styles/_breakpoints.scss` defines Tailwind breakpoint values as SCSS variables (e.g., `$breakpoint-md: 48rem`) for use in SCSS mixins. This is the ONLY place where `rem` values are allowed as SCSS variables, because Sass cannot use Tailwind's `screen()` function.

## Global Layout Tokens

Reusable layout dimensions live as CSS custom properties in `global.css` under `:root`. NEVER define them as local SCSS variables inside a single module.

```css
/* global.css */
:root {
  --layout-rail-width: 4.5rem;
  --layout-sidebar-width: 16.25rem;
}
```

## SCSS Modules — @reference + @apply + --primer-* vars

Every `.module.scss` uses `@reference` for Tailwind layout utilities and `--primer-*` CSS custom properties (injected via `useTheme` at Shell level) for colors:

```scss
@reference "tailwindcss/theme";
@reference "tailwindcss/utilities";

.root {
  @apply flex flex-col items-center p-4 gap-2 rounded-md;
  background-color: var(--primer-canvas-default);
  color: var(--primer-fg-default);
}

.emphasis {
  background-color: var(--primer-neutral-emphasis-plus);
  color: var(--primer-fg-on-emphasis);
}
```

## What is FORBIDDEN

```scss
// FORBIDDEN — hardcoded color
.card { color: #333; }

// FORBIDDEN — Tailwind color utilities
.card { @apply bg-neutral-900 text-white; }

// FORBIDDEN — Primer CSS vars directly (they don't work in the DOM)
.card { color: var(--fgColor-default); }
.card { background-color: var(--bgColor-emphasis); }

// FORBIDDEN — arbitrary Tailwind values when Primer has a prop
// (e.g., use <Text size="small"> instead of @apply text-[0.625rem])

// FORBIDDEN — raw CSS values that Tailwind provides as utilities
.item { opacity: 0.7; }
.item { width: 0; }
.item:active { transform: scale(0.95); }
.item { display: none; }
.item { display: block; }

// FORBIDDEN — raw CSS transitions
.item { transition: opacity 200ms ease; }

// FORBIDDEN — filter: brightness() cascades to ALL children, breaks nested components
.darker { filter: brightness(0.75); }

// REQUIRED — Tailwind for layout, --primer-* for colors
.card {
  @apply p-4 min-h-screen rounded-md;
  background-color: var(--primer-canvas-default);
  color: var(--primer-fg-default);
}
.item { @apply opacity-70; }
.item { @apply w-0; }
.item:active { @apply scale-95; }
.item { @apply hidden; }
.item { @apply block; }
.item { @apply transition-all duration-200 ease-in-out; }
```

## The Rule

1. If Tailwind has a utility for layout/spacing/transition properties → use `@apply`
2. If it's a color (background, foreground, border color, overlay) → use `--primer-*` CSS custom properties (injected via `useTheme` at Shell level)
3. If a darker/lighter shade is needed → use a different Primer token (e.g., `canvas-inset` < `canvas-default` < `canvas-subtle`). NEVER use `filter: brightness()` — it cascades to ALL children and breaks nested components
4. If a Primer component has a built-in prop for it → use the prop instead of CSS
   Always check Primer docs FIRST: `<Text size="small">` instead of custom CSS

## TypeScript / TSX — No Magic Numbers

- `@typescript-eslint/no-magic-numbers` is enforced (tests excluded)
- Extract ALL meaningful numbers into named constants
- Allowed raw values: `0`, `1`, `-1`

```typescript
// FORBIDDEN
const timeout = 1000 * 60

// REQUIRED
const ONE_SECOND_MS = 1000
const ONE_MINUTE_S = 60
const TIMEOUT_MS = ONE_SECOND_MS * ONE_MINUTE_S
```

## No Hardcoded Strings

- ALL user-facing strings use i18n (`useTranslation`) — see i18n rule
- API endpoints, config values, and keys MUST be constants or enums
- Route paths MUST be `as const` objects — NEVER hardcoded strings in `<Link to>` or `path:` props
- State machine statuses MUST be enums — NEVER string literals like `'loading'` or `'idle'`
- Error codes MUST use existing enums (e.g., `AuthErrorCode.UNKNOWN`) — NEVER hardcoded strings

```typescript
// FORBIDDEN — magic strings
setStatus('idle')
setError('UNKNOWN')
<Link to="/create-account">

// REQUIRED — enums and constants
setStatus(LoginStatus.Idle)
setError(AuthErrorCode.UNKNOWN)
<Link to={LoginRoutes.CreateAccount}>
```

## Enforcement

- **Stylelint** `declaration-strict-value`: fails on hardcoded colors, font-size, font-weight, line-height, border-radius, box-shadow, z-index
- **ESLint** `no-magic-numbers`: fails on raw numbers in TS/TSX (tests excluded)
- Both run in CI — violations block merge
